value.value: Mevalonate kinase (396 aa, ~42 kDa) is encoded by the human MVK gene. This protein is involved in the phosphorylation of mevalonate producing mevalonate 5-phosphate.
This gene plays a role in the removal of linear polyubiquitin chains from protein substrates.

Human OTULIN wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 5p15.2 and is approximately 56 kb in length. This allele, which encodes ubiquitin thioesterase otulin protein, is involved in the modulation of inflammation and deubiquitination. Mutation of the gene is associated with autoinflammation, panniculitis and dermatosis syndrome (AIPDS).
Ubiquitin thioesterase otulin (352 aa, ~40 kDa) is encoded by the human OTULIN gene. This protein plays a role in the downregulation of both protein ubiquitination and inflammation.

A radioconjugate composed of FAP-2286, a fibroblast activation protein (FAP)-targeted peptide, attached to a linker and tetraazacyclododecane tetraacetic acid chelator, conjugated to the radioisotope gallium Ga 68, with potential use as a tracer for FAP-expressing cancer-associated fibroblasts (CAFs) during positron emission tomography (PET). Upon administration of gallium Ga 68 FAP-2286, the FAP-2286 moiety targets and binds to FAP-expressing CAFs. Upon binding, FAP-expressing cells can be detected during PET imaging. FAP, a cell surface protein, is overexpressed on CAFs in the tumor microenvironment (TME).
This gene is involved in cytoskeletal modeling and immunoregulation.

Human PSTPIP1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 15q24.3 and is approximately 44 kb in length. This allele, which encodes proline-serine-threonine phosphatase-interacting protein 1, plays a role in immunoregulation and actin polymerization. Mutation of the gene is associated with pyogenic sterile arthritis, pyoderma gangrenosum, and acne syndrome (PAPAS).
A nuclear imaging method used to evaluate pathological bone metabolism.

Proline-serine-threonine phosphatase-interacting protein 1 (416 aa, ~48 kDa) is encoded by the human PSTPIP1 gene. This protein is involved in the regulation of actin polymerization and the immune response.

label.value: T-Cells and Natural Killer Cells Absent B-Cells Normal

value.value: A hematology test result indicating that a subject has a normal amount of B-cells but both T-cells and natural killer cells are either absent or found at abnormally low amounts.

label.value: T-Cells Absent, T-Cell Receptor Signaling Defective and Natural Killer Cells and B-Cells Normal

value.value: A hematology test result indicating that a subject has a normal amount of B-cells and natural killer cells but T-cells are absent or found at abnormally low amounts and a defect in T-cell receptor signaling pathways has been observed.

label.value: T-Cells, B-Cells and Natural Killer Cells Absent

value.value: A hematology test result indicating that a subject's T-cells, B-cells and natural killer cells are either absent or found at abnormally low amounts.
The reemergence of a low grade astrocytoma after a period of remission.

label.value: T-Cells Absent and Normal Natural Killer Cells and B-Cells

value.value: A hematology test result indicating that a subject has a normal amount of B-cells and natural killer cells but T-cells are either absent or found at abnormally low amounts.

label.value: T-Cells and B-Cells Absent and Natural Killer Cells Normal

value.value: A hematology test result indicating that a subject has a normal amount of natural killer cells but B-cells and T-cells are either absent or found at abnormally low amounts.
An extremely rare chondrosarcoma arising from the synovium either as a de novo neoplasm or secondary to synovial chondromatosis.
This gene is involved in adenine nucleotide metabolism and cellular energy homeostasis.
A measurement methodology in which a ruler device is used for measuring distance, consisting of an elongated piece of material marked with units of length.
A radiologic procedure to examine the structure and/or function of the liver in which a small amount of a radiopharmaceutical is injected into the bloodstream to illuminate the area for the scanner.

A measurement methodology in which a caliper device is used for measuring the length of dimension, consisting of two hinged legs (that may be inturned or outturned) usually, but not always, attached to a ruled scale, dial, or digital display.
A measurement methodology in which a pH meter device is used for measuring the alkalinity or acidity of a liquid or semi-solid substance.

Human AK2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1p35.1 and is approximately 73 kb in length. This allele, which encodes adenylate kinase 2, mitochondrial protein, plays a role in cellular energy homeostasis and adenine nucleotide metabolism. Mutation of the gene is associated with reticular dysgenesis.

label.value: Modified Health Care Climate Questionnaire for Breast Cancer Treatment

value.value: A shortened version of the Health Care Climate Questionnaire (HCCQ) adapted for breast cancer patients. It uses 6 questions and a 7-point Likert scale to measure the patient's perception of their physician's support for patient autonomy.

label.value: Feel that Physician Provided Choices and Options for Breast Cancer Treatment

value.value: A question about whether an individual feels or felt that their physician provided choices and options for their breast cancer treatment.

label.value: Feel that Physician Understood How I Saw Things with Respect to Breast Cancer

value.value: A question about whether an individual feels or felt that their physician understood how they saw things with respect to their breast cancer.
Different than the one(s) previously specified or mentioned.

label.value: Feel that Physician Expressed Confidence in my Ability to Make Decisions

value.value: A question about whether an individual feels or felt that their physician expressed confidence in their ability to make decisions.

label.value: Feel that Physician Listened to how I would Like to Handle Breast Cancer Treatment

value.value: A question about whether an individual feels or felt that their physician listened to how they would like to handle their breast cancer treatment.

label.value: Feel that Physician Encouraged Me to Ask Questions

value.value: A question about whether an individual feels or felt that their physician encouraged them to ask questions.

label.value: Feel that Physician Tried to Understand How I Saw Things Before Offering Opinion

value.value: I feel that my physician tried to understand how I saw things before offering an opinion

Adenylate kinase 2, mitochondrial (239 aa, ~26 kDa) is encoded by the human AK2 gene. This protein is involved in the reversible transfer of a phosphate group from ATP to AMP to form two ADP molecules.
This gene plays a role in budding of vesicles from the Golgi membrane, T- and NK-cell degranulation and intracellular trafficking.

Human AP3D1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 19p13.3 and is approximately 63 kb in length. This allele, which encodes AP-3 complex subunit delta-1 protein, is involved in T- and NK-cell degranulation, intracellular trafficking and Golgi membrane vesicle budding. Mutation of the gene is associated with Hermansky-Pudlak syndrome 10.

AP-3 complex subunit delta-1 (1153 aa, ~130 kDa) is encoded by the human AP3D1 gene. This protein plays a role in intracellular trafficking, Golgi membrane vesicle budding and degranulation of T- and NK-cells.
The act of making contact in order to propose, request, or suggest something.
